description: In 1618, the Joseon Dynasty carried out the project of repairing the outer wall of the era, and set up the Gwanggyo Castle in 1656. The piers of this fortress were only completed in 1679. In 1745, it was rebuilt into a complete stone city, with a city gate at that time. Guang Castle was severely attacked when Xinweiyang harassed it. On April 24, 1871, Will Rogers of the United States led a fleet of 1,230 troops to attack in order to demand trade. The troops successfully occupied Caozhiling and Dejin. After the town, they met the Korean army at Guang Castle again.
